query.result:
46 “Have no fear,” said my lord;
47 make yourself secure, because we are at a good point;
48 do not constrict, but expand every strength.

49 You are now arrived at the Purgatory:
50 see there the cliff that closes it around;
51 see the entrance there where it appears separated.

52 Shortly before, in the dawn that proceeds to the day,
53 when your soul was sleeping within,
54 over the flowers where it is adorned down there

55 came a woman, and said: “I am Lucy;
56 let me take this one who sleeps;
57 thus will I help him on his way.”

58 Sordello remained and the other gentle people;
59 she took you, and as the day was clear,
60 then she came upwards; and I along her footprints.

61 Here she placed you, but before they showed to me
62 her beautiful eyes that opened entrance;
63 then she and the sleep went away together.

