109 Devoutly I threw myself at the holy feet;
110 mercy I asked and that he open to me,
111 but three times in the chest first he gave to me.

115 Ashes, or earth that dry is taken,
116 of a color outside with its garment;
117 and from below from that he drew two keys.

118 One was of gold and the other was of silver;
